content.problemStatement:
A **negative step range** in Java allows a **for loop** to iterate **in reverse order**, decrementing the loop variable instead of incrementing it. This is useful for **countdowns, reverse sequences, and processing elements in reverse order** efficiently.  

**Syntax:**  
```java
for (int i = start; i >= end; i -= step) {
    // Code to execute in each iteration
}
```

---

**Example:**
```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Loop from 20 to 10, decreasing by 2 in each iteration
        for (int i = 20; i >= 10; i -= 2) {
            System.out.println(i); // Print the current value
        }
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**  
```default
20  
18  
16  
14  
12  
10  
```

